# The daily GitHub Action regenerates and commits these files. They change on
# both ends (CI + local), so on a merge they would conflict constantly.
# Mark them to always take the INCOMING (CI / remote) version instead of
# producing conflict markers.
#
# This needs the "theirs" merge driver registered once per clone (see README /
# the message below):
#   git config merge.theirs.name "take incoming version"
#   git config merge.theirs.driver "cp -f %B %A"
data/opportunities_db.json merge=theirs
data/sources_db.json        merge=theirs
docs/opportunities.js       merge=theirs
